Morpho governance funds public goods. The RFC needs to answer: why should this be grant-funded rather than venture-funded or bootstrapped?

The answer is that **collateral transparency is a commons problem**. No individual curator has sufficient incentive to build universal decomposition infrastructure — each curator only needs to understand their own vaults. But depositors need cross-curator, cross-vault transparency to make informed allocation decisions. The grant funds the public layer; the team can monetize the professional layer (premium API, real-time alerts, custom analysis) independently.

This argument is implicit in the RFC but never stated. It should be explicit, in the first page, because it's the strongest justification for grant funding over private capital.

