## Highest-Priority Pre-Submission Task

**Retroactive incident case study.** Show — with dated onchain state and specific reads — that existing tooling would have surfaced USD0++, xUSD, or Resolv/USR fragility before the incidents. This single artifact converts the proposal from "fund us to build a theory" to "fund us to operationalize a capability that would have prevented real losses."

---

## Unresolved (Team Must Decide)

- **Budget sizing:** $150-180K/9mo (safer) vs $225-250K/12mo (viable only with gated tranches and FTE commitment)
- **Model detail in main RFC:** strip entirely vs ~200-word summary pointing to technical appendix
- **Entity question:** named individuals as "independent research and tooling collective" vs registering a formal entity before submission

---

## The Simplest Test

> If a skeptical Morpho delegate asks "What can you show me working this week?", the answer must occupy the center of the RFC, not page seven.

